Tomorrow is my baby’s birthday which means it is one year since the single most transformative day of my life: The day my soul transcended above all of my fears and beyond whatever this earth life is and into the realm beyond of infiniteness and limitless existence. The day I learned my strength and my power. 

The day I gave birth. The day I was reborn. 

Birth was never once described to me this way. If I knew how much birth was going to strengthen, empower and heal me, I probably would have done it a lot sooner lol. If you are doing "all the things" but not popping off, listen up.

I have been there.

Back in 2020 I decided (like everyone else) to start a TikTok account. I followed all of the rules. I posted every day. I copied the latest trends and optimized my hashtags. I even tried to learn Renegade. (No, I will not be linking the video here, lmao)

I was doing everything. And nothing. Was. Working.

No one was seeing my posts. Well...not no one. Even though I was stuck in 200 view jail, somehow my friends and family members were seeing my posts and one of them even accidentally dm'd me a screenshot of it making fun of me (cue internal screaming, crying and throwing up)

It was humiliating. And then I finally DID have a post blow up!

Except...it blew up on the...WRONG side of TikTok. I went viral in a bad way.

Suddenly I was getting haters threatening me and making fun of me.

It was even more humiliating.

So I just decided to give up on creating a following and instead just stick to my podcast, where I felt safe, even though it wasn't really growing.

But today, I have an extremely loyal community that loves and supports me (and pays my bills). Hundreds of new people find me every single day. Members of my audience stop me on the street to say hi and give me hugs, thanking me for my content.

Swipe to see the before and after. 

So how did I do this?

I learned how to tap into Celebrity Energy. By rewiring my brain and hacking my nervous system, I learned how to feel safe being seen by massive amounts of people.

And when I did that, I became magnetic. People I've never met care about me.

That's the power of tapping into Celebrity Energy.

If you want to create massive levels of fame, it is available for you.

Your desires are your destiny.

All you have to do is tap into your unique magnetism.

If you want to learn how to do this too, dm me the words CELEBRITY. This week I’m taking 3 new artists, creatives and influencers who are ready to create massive levels of fame, success and impact.

In this week’s episode of How to Be Famous I’m sharing the one practice you can implement today to collapse the timeline of your fame and make your fame inevitable and instant. #podcast #howtobefamous #theartistsway #creativehealing #growoninstagram

Our brains always want to focus on the past, and on what we are missing, or lacking—the gap between expectation and reality. Our brains do this because it thinks that it is helpful: that if we somehow stare at all of the things we are missing, we will be able to make improvements. 

But what we focus on expands. 

When we focus on all that we are missing and lacking, we lose out on the present moment. 

Just 12 months from now, everything could be completely different in your life. You could fall in love, move cities, expand your family, get a new job, go viral…or even all of the above. 

This one question inspired me to take a solo trip to Paris. 

What parts of your holiday season would you savor if you knew things wouldn’t be the same next year? #theartistsway #creativehealing #journalprompts

I remember that it used to be SO f*cking triggering to go home for the holidays.

Everyone was asking me “so what have you been up to this year” but it felt like they were asking me “so...when are you going to give up get a real job?”

It was...hard. To say the least.

So between now and the end of the year, I am doing a free 10-day challenge to help YOU, the talented artists, creatives and influencers of the world use this time specifically to feel better, jumpstart your 2024, and tap into Celebrity Energy.

For the next 10 days, I’ll be posting a daily dose of inspiration as well as a little action item that will help you tap into Celebrity Energy during this next week.

Starting...now!

Did you know that being around your family is actually the best time to become famous?

That’s because to become famous, you don’t need more audition opportunities, better hashtags, or a team of rockstar agents.

What you DO need is Celebrity Energy - the energy that makes you magnetic to followers, audiences and even gatekeepers.

And the BEST time to develop it is when you are around your family.

Because your family only knows the PAST versions of you. The version of you that was created by your past behaviors, thoughts, emotions and actions, but that exists in the 3D, present reality. 

And to create fame, and step into Celebrity Energy, you have to step into a FUTURE version of yourself: you have to embody a version of yourself that doesn’t actually exist yet.

It’s trippy. And it’s fun.

So while you may get MAJORLY triggered around your family, this is actually the MOST powerful arena for you to practice your Celebrity Energy in. 
 
So. Here’s your first exercise:

I want you to write a list of 35 things that you created or accomplished over this past year. Get a paper and a pen and write it down. 

And hear me when I say: nothing is too small to go on this list.

35 is kind of an arbitrary number. But it’s also kind of a lot and it’s going to stretch your brain to look for any and all evidence that you are closer than you think to creating the fame, success, and following that you are meant for.

Ready? LFG!

The reason most people don’t hit their New Year’s goals is because they don’t set the proper foundation. Set yourself up for success by taking some time to do one (or all!) of these:

 1. Write a thank you text or email to the 5 people who impacted your year the most positively over the last year. 

2. Write your past self a thank you note for all that you accomplished and overcame over this past year. Include all of the ways that you surprised yourself and tell them how proud of them you are. 

3. Write a list of everything and everyone you want to forgive and set the intention to release and let it go (remember forgiveness is a gift you give YOURSELF!) If it’s safe, burn the list. 🔥

4. Write down the 10 best moments you celebrated over the past year, how you created those moments 

5. Listen to the replay of yesterday’s live training on the How to Be Famous podcast 🫶✨
